author: Paul Walsh
title: Woman killed in Brooklyn Center hotel room was 18-year-old from St. Cloud
text:
The woman killed in a Brooklyn Center hotel room over the weekend has been identified as an 18-year-old from St. Cloud.
Allie Marie Campbell died Saturday of a gunshot wound at the Quality Inn, 1600 James Circle N., the Hennepin County medical examiner's office said Tuesday.
Six people ages 19 to 23 were booked Sunday into the Hennepin County jail on suspicion of murder in connection with the case. Charges had not been filed against the four men and two women, and authorities have yet to release a motive behind her death.
Three of the suspects are from Brooklyn Park, two from Brooklyn Center and one from Crystal. They were arrested on traffic stops, police Cmdr. Richard Gabler said.
The shooting was reported to police about 8:45 p.m. Saturday. The woman was declared dead at the scene, police said.
"Brooklyn Center police do not believe this to be a random crime and are not currently seeking additional suspects," police said in a statement Sunday.
A gun was seized, but Gabler said it's not known whether it's the firearm used in the shooting.
According to audio from law enforcement dispatch, a hotel worker found the victim on the floor in the room.
The hotel is just north of Interstate 694, east of Shingle Creek Parkway and across the street from the Twin Cities offices of the FBI.
